Defendant David A Hassman in court with attorney Nicole Williams Buttery.   Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.    The victim addresses the Court.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 MONTHS JAIL (CREDIT - 5 days);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR; (the court would consider early termination of probation after 9 months at the recommendation of the agent).

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Any and all terms deemed appropriate by the agent (including if AODA assessment and anger mangement counseling are needed).
*Perform 50 hours community service.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);
